HEADWORD: Wedge-shaped
<hw>Wedge"-shaped`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the shape of a wedge; cuneiform.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Broad and truncate at the summit,
and tapering down to the base; <as>as, a <ex>wedge-shaped</ex>
leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wedge-shell</ent>⟦br⟧
